      <h1 class='title'>Piteairn Island</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 07 September 2004 vol 424 c97WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_97ws' title='Col. 97WS &mdash; HC Deb 07 September 2004 vol 424 c97WS' name='column_97ws' href='#column_97ws' rel='bookmark'>97WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040907_CWS_1'>  </a>
        <blockquote class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <cite class='member author entry-title unmatched-member'>The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for International Development (Mr. Gareth Thomas)</cite>
          <p class="first-para">Following detailed engineering assessment and design work over the past 12 months or so, I have set aside a total of &#x00A3;1.9 million from DFID funds to repair and refurbish the Hill of Difficulty road and the jetty/slipway in Pitcairn Island. Preparations are now in hand, with a view to expected commencement of the work in November of this year. In addition to this assistance, we will continue to provide medical and social welfare support for the island community.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
